SIMPLE: noodle
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Noodle
<hw>Noo"dle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Noddle</er>,
<er>Noddy</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A simpleton; a blockhead; a
stupid person; a ninny.</def> <mark>[Low]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The chuckling grin of <qex>noodles</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sydney
Smith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The head; also, <altname>noddle</altname>; -- used
jocosely or contemptuously; <as>as, use your
<ex>noodle</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> noggin.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Noodle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Noodle
<hw>Noo"dle</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G. <ets>nudel</ets>
vermicelli.]</ety> <def>A thin strip of dough, made with eggs, rolled
up, cut into small pieces, and used in soup.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nook</ent>⟦br⟧
